  <h2>Infant Water Safety Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Always use cold water:</strong> Hot tap water dissolves more lead and other contaminants from pipes. Filter cold water and heat it separately for formula preparation.</li>
    <li><strong>Flush pipes before use:</strong> Run the cold tap for 30 seconds before collecting water for formula, especially first thing in the morning. This clears stagnant water that has been sitting in your pipes overnight.</li>
    <li><strong>Follow filter replacement schedules strictly:</strong> A spent filter can release trapped contaminants. When filtering for an infant, replace filters on or before their rated expiration.</li>
    <li><strong>Discuss fluoride with your pediatrician:</strong> RO systems remove fluoride, which supports dental development. If you use RO water for formula exclusively, ask your pediatrician about fluoride supplements starting at 6 months.</li>
